    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1112"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1112">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.48/1857.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Consul <persName type="to">Canada</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 25, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your September 22. As the reasons which influenced this Government heretofore to
                    furnish assistance and transportation to American citizens in Mexico appear to
                    exist no longer, you are instructed to decline hereafter all such applications.
                    Repeat substance of this telegram to Consul, Tampico, for his information and
                    guidance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
